<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-71-0895 </DOCNO><TEXT>In October 1987, the European Commission published a Proposal for a CouncilRecommendation to Member States on developing the exploitation of renewableenergy sources in the Community. In the United Kingdom, a House of LordsSelect Committee was appointed to consider these Community Recommendationstaking evidence from bodies throughout the UK energy industry on matterssuch as prospects for renewable energy, potential problems, the contributionto energy demand, economics and environmental considerations. The opinionsof the Committee were published in a report on 21 June 1988. This articlegives an edited summary of the background and views of witnesses andthe opinions of the Select Committee. The renewable energy sources coveredincluded wind power, biomass, geothermal energy, solar energy, tidalpower, wave power and combined heat and power.</TEXT></DOC>